Title: Tax and Liquidity Effects in Pricing Government Bonds 
Abstract:
 Daily data from interdealer government bond brokers are examined for tax
 and liquidity effects. We use two approaches to create cash flow matching
 portfolios of similar securities and look for pricing discrepancies
 associated with liquidity or tax effects. We also look for the presence of
 tax and liquidity effects by including a liquidity term when fitting a
 cubic spline to the after-tax yield curve. We find evidence of tax timing
 options and liquidity effects. However, the effects are much smaller than
 previously reported and the effects of liquidity are primarily due to high
 volume bonds with long maturities. Copyright The American Finance Association 1998. 
